-- Chinese Company Interested in Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer, Beijing News Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-07T00:24:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-07/chinese-company-interested-in-metro-goldwyn-mayer-beijing-news-reports.html
A Chinese company is interested in
buying a stake in Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Studios Inc., the
distributor of the James Bond and Rocky movies, after the U.S.
company issues new shares as part of a plan to emerge from
bankruptcy, Beijing News reported, citing Zhou Tiedong, general
manager of the marketing division of China Film Group Corp.  Zhou declined to identify the company and said that a U.S.
law firm is handling the transaction, the paper reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  